son Button]] was added to the range during April 2010.<ref name=\"brandrepublic.com\"/><ref name=\"marketingmagazine.co.uk\"/><ref name=\"socialshopping.com\"/><ref name=\"marksandspencer9\"/> Both were only available in bigger stores, but were only available on line in late 2010.\n\n'''World Cup'''\n* World Cup (2002/2006/2010)- Periodical [[FIFA World Cup|World cup]] (some media critics said [[Fascist]]) memorabilia and [[merchandise]] for kids.<ref name=\"marksandspencer10\"/>\n\n'''Plus fit'''\n* Plus fit- Was launched in selected stores during July 2010 and are large sized children's clothes. It has proven to be a very popular line.<ref name=\"findarticles.com\">[http://findarticles.com/p/news-articles/mail-on-sunday-london-england-the/mi_8003/is_2010_July_25/supersize-school-uniforms-obesity-epidemic/ai_n54568822/] {{Dead link|date=February 2011|bot=RjwilmsiBot}}</ref><ref name=\"findarticles.com\"/><ref name=\"thefamilygp.com\"/><ref name=\"health.virginmedia.com\"/>\n\n'''Party, Party, Party!'''\n* Party, Party, Party! \u2013 seasonal party clothes; reduced to women's wear in 2012<ref name=\"auto3\"/>\n\n'''Ready to play'''\n* Ready to play [[Romper suit|playwear]]<ref name=\"auto2\">{{cite web |url=http://www.marksandspencer.com/Ready-to-Play-Young-Girls-1-7-yrs-childrenswear/b/245362031 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20130128064549/http://www.marksandspencer.com/Ready-to-Play-Young-Girls-1-7-yrs-childrenswear/b/245362031 |url-status=dead |archive-date=2013-01-28 |title=Ready to Play YG : OLD : childrenswear : Pending : Archive : 42964030 : Marks & Spencer |publisher=Marksandspencer.com |accessdate=2009-11-07 }}</ref>\n\n'''Sleep'''\n* Sleep \u2013 children's [[Nightwear|night clothes]]\n\n'''Casual'''\n* Casual \u2013 children's [[casual clothes]] and shoes\n\n'''Partyware'''\n* Partyware \u2013 children's party clothes<ref name=\"marksandspencer3\"/>\n\n'''Denim''' \n* Denim \u2013 children's jeans\n\n'''The Shirt-sleeve empire'''\n* The Shirt-sleeve empire \u2013 boys' shirts (was only available online in 2010)\n\nBoth Sleepwear, Twinkle toes, Casual Junior, The Shirt-sleeve empire, Partyware and Occasionwear were all merged into either Occasions, Indigo Junior or Autograph Junior over the Festive season of 2010\u20132011.\n\n===Other babywear lines===\nM&S markets its miscellaneous and specialist babywear under the following brand names:\n\n* Babywear \u2013 unisex hats, gloves, socks, shoes and cot linen\n* Petite babe \u2013 unisex small and premature babies\n* Pure cotton \u2013  pure cotton unisex baby clothes\n* Ready to play \u2013 [[Romper suit|playwear]]<ref name=\"auto2\"/>\n* Romper-suit republic \u2013 baby clothes (was only available online until 2011)\n* Fashion \u2013 babies' [[fashion clothes]]\n\n'''Babywear''' was reduced to woolly hats, gloves, socks and bed linen- after its [[infant bodysuit|baby clothes]], [[blanket sleeper]]s, [[Romper suit]]s, cot [[blanket]]s, babies' [[Bib (garment)|bib]]s, non-woolly hats, socks and cot linen were turned in the '''Indigo Baby''' line, along with Romper-suit republic and Fashion in the January 2011.\n\n=== Breakthrough Breast Cancer ===\nM&S periodically markets charitable clothes for Breakthrough Breast Cancer.<ref name=\"breakthrough.org.uk\"/>\n\n* [[Breakthrough Breast Cancer|B.C.A.UK]] (on line charitable T-shirts for the under 40's).\n* [[Breakthrough Breast Cancer|B.C.A.M.]] (charitable merchandise aimed at raising awareness of [[breast cancer]]).\n\n===Revamped lines===\nApril 2013 saw the M&S lingerie chief, Janie Schaffer, quit after only months in the job.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-22166323 |title=M&S lingerie chief Janie Schaffer leaves after three months |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2013-04-16 |accessdate=2013-07-22}}</ref>\n\n15 May 2013 saw the launch of the 'Best of British range' as well as the overhaul of Per Una and Indigo.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/money/city-news/marks-spencer-fashion-launch-slick-1889943|title=Graham Hiscott verdict Marks and Spencer fashion launch was slick but what matters is what core customers think|first=Graham|last=Hiscott|date=15 May 2013}}</ref>\n<ref name=\"mirror2\">{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/money/city-news/marks-spencer-fashion-launch-slick-1889943 |title=Marks and Spencer fashion launch was slick but what matters is what core customers think: Graham Hiscott verdict \u2013 Graham Hiscott \u2013 Mirror Online |work=Daily Mirror |date=2013-05-15 |accessdate=2013-07-22}}</ref> Patrick Bousquet-Chavanne \u2013 currently M&S's corporate director of strategy implementation and business development became the new marketing director and wii succeed Steven Sharp in July. Mark Bolland also vowed to bring \"quality and style back\"<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-22546823 |title=M&S tries to boost sales with new clothing range |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2013-05-15 |accessdate=2013-07-22}}</ref><ref name=\"Emma Simpson\">{{cite news|author=Emma Simpson |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-22533986 |title=M&S tries to lure back shoppers with new fashion ranges |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2013-05-14 |accessdate=2013-07-22}}</ref><ref name=\"BBC News\">{{cite news| url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-22605609 | work=BBC News | title=Marks and Spencer profits fall as clothing disappoints | date=21 May 2013}}</ref>\n\nThe chain already has 20 UK suppliers and is looking to increase that number.<ref name=\"mirror2\"/>\n\n==Shoes==\n'''Men'''\n* Collezione (men)\n* Airflex (men)\n\n'''Women'''\n* Insola (women)\n* Classic (women)\n* Footglove (women)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.marksandspencer.com/Shoes-Womenswear/b/43126030?ie=UTF8&intid=gnav_women_shoes |title=Shoes : Womenswear : Marks & Spencer |publisher=Marksandspencer.com |accessdate=2009-11-07}}</ref>\n* Limited Collection (women)\n* Per Una (women)\n* Portfolio (women)\n* Shoes, shoes, shoes (women) high-end shoes\n\n''