er=Marksandspencer.com |date= |accessdate=2009-11-07 }}{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nIt has a sub-brand product range called '''Denim''' which deals with women's jeans.<ref name=\"thisismoney.co.uk\"/><ref name=\"dailymail.co.uk\"/>\n\n'''Babywear''' was reduced to woolly hats, gloves, socks and bed linen after its [[infant bodysuit|baby clothes]], [[blanket sleeper]]s, [[Romper suit]]s, cot [[blanket]]s, babies' [[Bib (garment)|bib]]s, non-woolly hats, socks and cot linen were turned into the '''Indigo Baby''' line in January 2011.\n\n===Autograph===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Brand!! Line!!Customer gender!! Products!!Source(s)\n|-\n| Autograph (headed by [[John Powell (clothing designer)|John Powell]])|| \u2013 || Unisex || Unisex and/or mixed ranges of hats, belts, scarves, gloves, bags, plus women's lingerie, tunics and hosiery. Smart-casual clothing exclusively designed for M&S by designers such as Nigel Hall, [[Jeffery West]] and [[Timothy Everest]]. ||<ref name=\"marksintime\"/><ref name=\"thisismoney.co.uk\">{{cite web|last=Craven |first=Neil |url=http://www.thisismoney.co.uk/news/article.html?in_article_id=512068&in_page_id=2 |title=M&S clothing brands set for overhaul |publisher=This is Money |date=2010-08-15 |accessdate=2017-07-07}}</ref><ref name=\"dailymail.co.uk\">{{cite news| url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/money/article-1303143/Bollands-bonfire-M-S-brands.html | location=London | work=Daily Mail | first=Neil | last=Craven | title=Bolland's bonfire of the M&S brands | date=2010-08-16}}</ref><ref name=\"marksandspencer12\"/><ref name=\"marksandspencer12\"/><ref name=\"marksandspencer6\">{{cite web |url=http://www.marksandspencer.com/Autograph-Mens/b/43395030?ie=UTF8&ie=UTF8?ie=UTF8&pf_rd_r=0PENPG1YWAZ7CND6AK0M&pf_rd_m=A2BO0OYVBKIQJM&pf_rd_t=101&pf_rd_i=43371030&pf_rd_p=475115433&pf_rd_s=left-nav-2 |title=Autograph : Men's : Marks & Spencer |publisher=Marksandspencer.com |date= |accessdate=2011-07-18 