 = [[Free education]]\n|tuition                = \n|revenue                = \n|communities            = \n|feeders                = \n|main feeder school for = \n|graduates              =\n|affiliations           = \n|alumni                 = \n|nobel_laureates        = \n|information            = \n|homepage               = \n|url                    = \n|website                = \n|footnotes              = \n}}\n\n'''Vinayagapuram maha vidyalayam'''  ({{lang-ta|\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bbe\u0baf\u0b95\u0baa\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0b95\u0bbe \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd, \u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bcb\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd }})  is a public school located in [[Vinayagapuram, Sri Lanka]], [[List of schools in Eastern Province, Sri Lanka|Eastern Province, Sri Lanka]]<ref>[https://wikimili.com/en/List_of_schools_in_Eastern_Province%2C_Sri_Lanka'List of schools in eastern']</ref>. It was founded in 1965 and is one of the oldest schools in [[Vinayagapuram, Sri Lanka]].The school provides both [[Primary education|Primary]] and [[Secondary education]].\n==Principals==\n\n==References==\n\n{{Uncategorized|date=April 2020}}\n", "name_user": "\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bbf\u0bb4\u0ba9\u0bcd997", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200ePrincipals)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vinayagapuram_Maha_Vidyalayam"}
{"title_page": "Jakarta LRT", "text_new": "{{hatnote|Not to be confused with [[Greater Jakarta LRT]], a similar LRT system in Jakarta.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox public transit\n| name                 = Jakarta LRT\n| image                = LRT Jakarta Logo.png\n| alt                  = \n| imagesize            =\n| caption              = \n| image2               = LRT Jakarta - Hyundai Rotem LRV in Boulevard Utara Station.jpg\n| imagesize2           = 300px\n| alt2                 = \n| caption2             = Jakarta LRT at Boulevard Utara station\n| owner                = Government of Jakarta\n| area served          = \n| locale               = [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]]\n| transit_type         = [[Light metro]]\n| lines                = 1\n| line_number          = \n| start                = \n| end                  = \n| stations             = 6 (first phase)\n| ridership            = \n| annual_ridership     = \n| chief_executive      = \n| headquarters         = \n| website              = {{URL|www.lrtjakarta.co.id}}\n| began_operation      = 1 December 2019\n| operation_will_start = \n| operator             = PT LRT Jakarta\n| character            = Elevated\n| vehicles             = Eight two-car trainsets\n| headway              = 10 minutes\n| system_length        = {{convert|5.8|km|mi|abbr=on}} (first phase)<ref name=\"ramadhan\"/><br>{{convert|107.7|km|mi|abbr=on}} (total length)\n| track_gauge          = {{track gauge|1435mm|lk=on}}<ref name=\"ramadhan\">{{cite news |last1=Ramadhan |first1=Ardito |title=Ini Spesifikasi Kereta LRT yang Tiba di Jakarta |url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2018/04/14/05412541/ini-spesifikasi-kereta-lrt-yang-tiba-di-jakarta |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KOMPAS.com |date=14 April 2018 |language=id}}</ref>\n| el = 750V ([[Direct current|DC]]) [[third rail]]<ref name=\"zackyfahd\">{{cite news |last1=Fahd |first1=Zacky |title=Eksklusif: Ini Dia Foto Sarana Kereta LRT Jakarta Kelapa Gading \u2013 Velodrome! |url=https://www.kaorinusantara.or.id/newsline/100736/eksklusif-ini-dia-foto-sarana-kereta-lrt-jakarta-kelapa-gading-velodrome |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KAORI Nusantara |date=3 December 2017 |language=id}}</ref>\n| top_speed            = 60 km/h\n| map                  = {{LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|inline=y}}\n| map_name             = \n| map_state            = collapsed\n| box_width            = 300\n}}\nThe '''Jakarta Light Rail Transit''' ('''Jakarta LRT''') ([[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]: ''Lintas Rel Terpadu Jakarta'') is one of the [[Medium-capacity rail transport system|light metro]] system in [[Jakarta]], the capital city of [[Indonesia]]. It is being implemented by the Jakarta provincial government.<ref name=\"KP-LRT\">{{cite news | url=http://lipsus.kompas.com/topikpilihanlist/3414/1/rencana.lrt.di.jakarta | title=Rencana LRT di Jakarta | newspaper=Kompas | location=Jakarta | date=11 September 2015 | language=Indonesian | accessdate=21 September 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151011150858/http://lipsus.kompas.com/topikpilihanlist/3414/1/rencana.lrt.di.jakarta | archive-date=11 October 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref> Eight two-cars trainsets were procured. The first phase of the LRT, from [[Jakarta International Velodrome|Velodrome]] to [[Kelapa Gading]] began commercial operations on 1 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://en.tempo.co/read/1275107/lrt-jakarta-fare-to-be-valid-per-december-1 |title= https://en.tempo.co/read/1275107/lrt-jakarta-fare-to-be-valid-per-december-1 |work= Tempo |accessdate= 22 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\n[[File:LRT Jakarta - Hyundai Rotem LRV Leaving Velodrome Station.jpg|thumb|[[Hyundai Rotem]] [[Light rail|LRV]] leaving [[Jakarta International Velodrome|Velodrome]] station during a limited trial run on 7 September 2018]]\nThe Jakarta light rail transit project aims to tackle Jakarta's high road traffic congestion.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Eka |first1=Aditya |title=Laporan Perjalanan: Inilah Kesan Pertama Kereta LRT Jakarta - KAORI Nusantara |url=https://www.kaorinusantara.or.id/newsline/116274/kesan-pertama-kereta-lrt-jakarta |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KAORI Nusantara |date=13 September 2018 |language=id}}</ref> The rolling stock comes from [[Hyundai Rotem]] from South Korea. Each trainset consists of two cars and will be able to carry 270 to 278 passengers. There will be a total of 16 cars.<ref name=\"ramadhan\" />\n[[Platform screen doors]] by [[ST Engineering|ST Engineering Electronics]] will be installed at all stations.\n\nA public trial run began on 11 June 2019 between Boulevard Utara and Velodrome stations, with free admission to registered ticket holders.<ref>{{cite news |title=LRT Jakarta starts free public trial on Tuesday|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2019/06/09/lrt-jakarta-starts-free-public-trial-on-monday.html |date=10 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Network==\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 1 - Pegangsaan Dua - Velodrome, along 5.8&nbsp;km<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ekonomi.kompas.com/read/2018/08/24/084600826/kemenhub-lakukan-operasional-terbatas-untuk-lrt-kelapa-gading#|title=Kemenhub Lakukan Operasional Terbatas untuk LRT Kelapa Gading - Kompas.com|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|date=2018-08-24|work=KOMPAS.com|access-date=2018-09-07|language=id}}</ref>\n\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 2A - Pegangsaan Dua - Jakarta International Stadium, along 7.5 km\n\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 2B - Velodrome - Manggarai\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; color: black; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%\"\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"color:white\" bgcolor=\"#f39700\"\n|'''Station Number'''\n|'''Station Name'''\n|'''Interchange/Notes'''\n|-\n!colspan=3|Phase 1\n|-\n|S-01||Pegangsaan Dua||Terminus\n|-\n|S-02||Boulevard Utara||\n|-\n|S-03||Boulevard Selatan||\n|-\n|S-04||Pulomas||\n|-\n|S-05||Equestrian||\n|-\n|S-06||Velodrome||Terminus until the completion of Phase 2\n|-\n|}\n\nConstruction of Route 1 started on 22 June 2016. The first six kilometers of the route connecting the Kelapa Gading Depot to Velodrome Station was 29.61% complete by 26 June 2017. It was expected to be operational before the [[2018 Asian Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.en.netralnews.com/news/currentnews/read/6526/in.august.2018..kelapa.gading.rawamangun.lrt.to.commence.operation|title=In August 2018, Kelapa Gading-Rawamangun LRT to Commence Operation}}</ref> However, this did not happen as construction is not yet finished and the Indonesia Asian Games Organizing Committee (INASGOC) considered that buses would be more effective in transporting the athletes.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wuragil |first1=Zacharias |title=Duh, LRT Jakarta Akhirnya Gagal Ikut Asian Games |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/1116195/duh-lrt-jakarta-akhirnya-gagal-ikut-asian-games/full&view=ok |accessdate=26 August 2018 |work=Tempo |date=12 August 2018 |language=id}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=LRT gagal beroperasi saat Asian Games Jakarta |url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/700482/lrt-gagal-beroperasi-saat-asian-games-jakarta |accessdate=26 August 2018 |agency=[[Antara (news agency)|Antara]] |date=11 April 2018 |language=id}}</ref> \n\nThe test run for the LRT was initially scheduled for 10 August, however was delayed to 15 August 2018. Phase 1 was planned to begin operation in February, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Manurung |first1=M Yusuf |title=Kantongi Izin dari Kemenhub, Hari Ini LRT Uji Operasi |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/1117132/kantongi-izin-dari-kemenhub-hari-ini-lrt-uji-operasi/full&view=ok |accessdate=26 August 2018 |work=Tempo |date=15 August 2018 |language=id}}</ref>\nAfter several delays, the line opened for free public trial run from July to late November 2019. Commercial operations began on 1 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kartika |first1=Mimi |title=Peresmian LRT Jakarta Diundur, Ini Penjelasan Anies |url=https://nasional.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/jabodetabek-nasional/psiiuz409/peresmian-lrt-jakarta-diundur-ini-penjelasan-anies |accessdate=3 June 2019 |work=Republika Online |publisher=Republika Online |date=3 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.suara.com/news/2019/06/21/134208/skybridge-rampung-stasiun-lrt-velodrome-resmi-terintegrasi-halte-busway |title=Skybridge Rampung, Stasiun LRT Velodrome Resmi Terintegrasi Halte Busway |author=\nAgung Sandy Lesmana and Stephanus Aranditio |date=June 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Planned Line===\n*Kemayoran - Kelapa Gading along 21.6&nbsp;km\n*Joglo - Tanah Abang along 11&nbsp;km\n*Puri Kembangan - Tanah Abang along 9.3&nbsp;km\n*Pesing - Kelapa Gading along 20.7&nbsp;km\n*Pesing - Soekarno-Hatta Airport along 18.5&nbsp;km\n*Cempaka Putih - Ancol along 10&nbsp;km.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Jakarta MRT]]\n*[[Greater Jakarta LRT]]\n*[[Transport in Jakarta]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=40em}}\n{{Portal|Indonesia|Jakarta}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=735&v=gWhO5ENXh98 Jakarta LRT Progress video per May 2018]\n\n{{Urban Transit in Indonesia}}\n{{Urban Rail Transit in ASEAN}}\n{{Rapid transit in Asia}}\n\n[[Category:Rapid transit in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Transport in Jakarta]]\n[[Category:Rail infrastructure in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Rapid transit]]\n[[Category:Passenger rail transport]]\n[[Category:Railway companies of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 2019]]\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Light rail]]\n", "text_old": "{{hatnote|Not to be confused with [[Greater Jakarta LRT]], a similar LRT system in Jakarta.}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox public transit\n| name                 = Jakarta LRT\n| image                = LRT Jakarta Logo.png\n| alt                  = \n| imagesize            =\n| caption              = \n| image2               = LRT Jakarta - Hyundai Rotem LRV in Boulevard Utara Station.jpg\n| imagesize2           = 300px\n| alt2                 = \n| caption2             = Jakarta LRT at Boulevard Utara station\n| owner                = Government of Jakarta\n| area served          = \n| locale               = [[Jakarta]], [[Indonesia]]\n| transit_type         = [[Light metro]]\n| lines                = 1\n| line_number          = \n| start                = \n| end                  = \n| stations             = 6 (first phase)\n| ridership            = \n| annual_ridership     = \n| chief_executive      = \n| headquarters         = \n| website              = {{URL|www.lrtjakarta.co.id}}\n| began_operation      = 1 December 2019\n| operation_will_start = \n| operator             = PT LRT Jakarta\n| character            = Elevated\n| vehicles             = Eight two-car trainsets\n| headway              = 10 minutes\n| system_length        = {{convert|5.8|km|mi|abbr=on}} (first phase)<ref name=\"ramadhan\"/><br>{{convert|107.7|km|mi|abbr=on}} (total length)\n| track_gauge          = {{track gauge|1435mm|lk=on}}<ref name=\"ramadhan\">{{cite news |last1=Ramadhan |first1=Ardito |title=Ini Spesifikasi Kereta LRT yang Tiba di Jakarta |url=https://megapolitan.kompas.com/read/2018/04/14/05412541/ini-spesifikasi-kereta-lrt-yang-tiba-di-jakarta |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KOMPAS.com |date=14 April 2018 |language=id}}</ref>\n| el = 750V ([[Direct current|DC]]) [[third rail]]<ref name=\"zackyfahd\">{{cite news |last1=Fahd |first1=Zacky |title=Eksklusif: Ini Dia Foto Sarana Kereta LRT Jakarta Kelapa Gading \u2013 Velodrome! |url=https://www.kaorinusantara.or.id/newsline/100736/eksklusif-ini-dia-foto-sarana-kereta-lrt-jakarta-kelapa-gading-velodrome |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KAORI Nusantara |date=3 December 2017 |language=id}}</ref>\n| top_speed            = 60 km/h\n| map                  = {{LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|inline=y}}\n| map_name             = \n| map_state            = collapsed\n| box_width            = 300\n}}\nThe '''Jakarta Light Rail Transit''' ('''Jakarta LRT''') ([[Indonesian language|Indonesian]]: ''Lintas Rel Terpadu Jakarta'') is one of the [[Medium-capacity rail transport system|light metro]] system in [[Jakarta]], the capital city of [[Indonesia]]. It is being implemented by the Jakarta provincial government.<ref name=\"KP-LRT\">{{cite news | url=http://lipsus.kompas.com/topikpilihanlist/3414/1/rencana.lrt.di.jakarta | title=Rencana LRT di Jakarta | newspaper=Kompas | location=Jakarta | date=11 September 2015 | language=Indonesian | accessdate=21 September 2015 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20151011150858/http://lipsus.kompas.com/topikpilihanlist/3414/1/rencana.lrt.di.jakarta | archive-date=11 October 2015 | url-status=dead }}</ref>Eight two-cars trainsets were procured. The first phase of the LRT, from [[Jakarta International Velodrome|Velodrome]] to [[Kelapa Gading]] began commercial operations on 1 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://en.tempo.co/read/1275107/lrt-jakarta-fare-to-be-valid-per-december-1 |title= https://en.tempo.co/read/1275107/lrt-jakarta-fare-to-be-valid-per-december-1 |work= Tempo |accessdate= 22 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Background==\n[[File:LRT Jakarta - Hyundai Rotem LRV Leaving Velodrome Station.jpg|thumb|[[Hyundai Rotem]] [[Light rail|LRV]] leaving [[Jakarta International Velodrome|Velodrome]] station during a limited trial run on 7 September 2018]]\nThe Jakarta light rail transit project aims to tackle Jakarta's high road traffic congestion.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Eka |first1=Aditya |title=Laporan Perjalanan: Inilah Kesan Pertama Kereta LRT Jakarta - KAORI Nusantara |url=https://www.kaorinusantara.or.id/newsline/116274/kesan-pertama-kereta-lrt-jakarta |accessdate=2 November 2018 |work=KAORI Nusantara |date=13 September 2018 |language=id}}</ref> The rolling stock comes from [[Hyundai Rotem]] from South Korea. Each trainset consists of two cars and will be able to carry 270 to 278 passengers. There will be a total of 16 cars.<ref name=\"ramadhan\" />\n[[Platform screen doors]] by [[ST Engineering|ST Engineering Electronics]] will be installed at all stations.\n\nA public trial run began on 11 June 2019 between Boulevard Utara and Velodrome stations, with free admission to registered ticket holders.<ref>{{cite news |title=LRT Jakarta starts free public trial on Tuesday|url=https://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2019/06/09/lrt-jakarta-starts-free-public-trial-on-monday.html |date=10 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Network==\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 1 - Pegangsaan Dua - Velodrome, along 5.8&nbsp;km<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://ekonomi.kompas.com/read/2018/08/24/084600826/kemenhub-lakukan-operasional-terbatas-untuk-lrt-kelapa-gading#|title=Kemenhub Lakukan Operasional Terbatas untuk LRT Kelapa Gading - Kompas.com|last=Media|first=Kompas Cyber|date=2018-08-24|work=KOMPAS.com|access-date=2018-09-07|language=id}}</ref>\n\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 2A - Pegangsaan Dua - Jakarta International Stadium, along 7.5 km\n\n*{{RouteBox|LRT Line A|LRT Line A (Jakarta LRT)|#f39700}} Phase 2B - Velodrome - Manggarai\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\" style=\"margin-left: 1em; margin-bottom: 1em; color: black; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%\"\n|- align=\"center\" style=\"color:white\" bgcolor=\"#f39700\"\n|'''Station Number'''\n|'''Station Name'''\n|'''Interchange/Notes'''\n|-\n!colspan=3|Phase 1\n|-\n|S-01||Pegangsaan Dua||Terminus\n|-\n|S-02||Boulevard Utara||\n|-\n|S-03||Boulevard Selatan||\n|-\n|S-04||Pulomas||\n|-\n|S-05||Equestrian||\n|-\n|S-06||Velodrome||Terminus until the completion of Phase 2\n|-\n|}\n\nConstruction of Route 1 started on 22 June 2016. The first six kilometers of the route connecting the Kelapa Gading Depot to Velodrome Station was 29.61% complete by 26 June 2017. It was expected to be operational before the [[2018 Asian Games]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.en.netralnews.com/news/currentnews/read/6526/in.august.2018..kelapa.gading.rawamangun.lrt.to.commence.operation|title=In August 2018, Kelapa Gading-Rawamangun LRT to Commence Operation}}</ref> However, this did not happen as construction is not yet finished and the Indonesia Asian Games Organizing Committee (INASGOC) considered that buses would be more effective in transporting the athletes.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Wuragil |first1=Zacharias |title=Duh, LRT Jakarta Akhirnya Gagal Ikut Asian Games |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/1116195/duh-lrt-jakarta-akhirnya-gagal-ikut-asian-games/full&view=ok |accessdate=26 August 2018 |work=Tempo |date=12 August 2018 |language=id}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=LRT gagal beroperasi saat Asian Games Jakarta |url=https://www.antaranews.com/berita/700482/lrt-gagal-beroperasi-saat-asian-games-jakarta |accessdate=26 August 2018 |agency=[[Antara (news agency)|Antara]] |date=11 April 2018 |language=id}}</ref> \n\nThe test run for the LRT was initially scheduled for 10 August, however was delayed to 15 August 2018. Phase 1 was planned to begin operation in February, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Manurung |first1=M Yusuf |title=Kantongi Izin dari Kemenhub, Hari Ini LRT Uji Operasi |url=https://metro.tempo.co/read/1117132/kantongi-izin-dari-kemenhub-hari-ini-lrt-uji-operasi/full&view=ok |accessdate=26 August 2018 |work=Tempo |date=15 August 2018 |language=id}}</ref>\nAfter several delays, the line opened for free public trial run from July to late November 2019. Commercial operations began on 1 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Kartika |first1=Mimi |title=Peresmian LRT Jakarta Diundur, Ini Penjelasan Anies |url=https://nasional.republika.co.id/berita/nasional/jabodetabek-nasional/psiiuz409/peresmian-lrt-jakarta-diundur-ini-penjelasan-anies |accessdate=3 June 2019 |work=Republika Online |publisher=Republika Online |date=3 June 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.suara.com/news/2019/06/21/134208/skybridge-rampung-stasiun-lrt-velodrome-resmi-terintegrasi-halte-busway |title=Skybridge Rampung, Stasiun LRT Velodrome Resmi Terintegrasi Halte Busway |author=\nAgung Sandy Lesmana and Stephanus Aranditio |date=June 21, 2019}}</ref>\n\n=== Planned Line===\n*Kemayoran - Kelapa Gading along 21.6&nbsp;km\n*Joglo - Tanah Abang along 11&nbsp;km\n*Puri Kembangan - Tanah Abang along 9.3&nbsp;km\n*Pesing - Kelapa Gading along 20.7&nbsp;km\n*Pesing - Soekarno-Hatta Airport along 18.5&nbsp;km\n*Cempaka Putih - Ancol along 10&nbsp;km.\n\n==See also==\n*[[Jakarta MRT]]\n*[[Greater Jakarta LRT]]\n*[[Transport in Jakarta]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=40em}}\n{{Portal|Indonesia|Jakarta}}\n\n==External links==\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?time_continue=735&v=gWhO5ENXh98 Jakarta LRT Progress video per May 2018]\n\n{{Urban Transit in Indonesia}}\n{{Urban Rail Transit in ASEAN}}\n{{Rapid transit in Asia}}\n\n[[Category:Rapid transit in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Transport in Jakarta]]\n[[Category:Rail infrastructure in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Rapid transit]]\n[[Category:Passenger rail transport]]\n[[Category:Railway companies of Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Railway lines opened in 2019]]\n[[Category:2019 establishments in Indonesia]]\n[[Category:Light rail]]\n", "name_user": "TheGreatSG'rean", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Jakarta_LRT"}
{"title_page": "Fort Saskatchewan", "text_new": "{{short description|City in Alberta, Canada}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Fort Saskatchewan\n| official_name                   = City of Fort Saskatchewan\n| other_name                      = \n| native_name                     = <!--for cities with native name not in English-->\n| nickname                        = \n| settlement_type                 = City\n| motto                           = Gotta Love It!\n| image_skyline                   = Fort Saskatewan Public Library and City Hall - 31-Dec-2016.jpg\n| imagesize                       = 300px\n| image_caption                   = Fort Saskatchewan City Hall and Public Library in December, 2016\n| image_flag                      = Fort Saskatchewan-flag.png\n| flag_size                       = \n| image_seal                      = \n| seal_size                       = \n| image_blank_emblem              = Logo of Fort Saskatchewan, Alberta.svg\n| shield_size                     = \n| image_map                       = 0117 City Fort Saskatchewan, Alberta Locator.svg\n| mapsize                         = \n| map_caption                     = Location with Strathcona County\n| pushpin_map                     = Canada Alberta<!-- the name of a location map as per http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Template:Location_map -->\n| pushpin_label_position          = <!-- the position of the pushpin label: left, right, top, bottom, none -->\n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location of Fort Saskatchewan in [[Alberta]]\n| pushpin_mapsize                 = \n| subdivision_type                = Country\n| subdivision_name                = [[Canada]]\n| subdivision_type1               = [[Provinces and territories of Canada|Province]]\n| subdivision_name1               = [[Alberta]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of regions of Alberta|Region]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Edmonton Metropolitan Region]]\n| subdivision_type3        